graph atoms-guide {
  meta: { description: "Atoms guide prompt", type: "prompt", category: "ai", author: "AITOS Team" }

  let prompt = set(key: "_promptAtomsGuide", value: ">>> CONTEXT: This atom reference is ONLY needed when the user EXPLICITLY asks you to create or modify a graph. For normal conversation, ignore this section. <<<\n\n## Available Atoms\n\nCall getSkillSet() to get all available atoms. Key atoms include:\n\n### UI Atoms (from @aitos/output)\n- createElement(tag, id) - Create DOM element\n- appendChild(parentId, childId) - Append child to parent\n- removeElement(id) - Remove element\n- setStyles(id, styles) - Set CSS styles (object)\n- setTextContent(id, text) - Set text content\n- setInnerHTML(id, html) - Set inner HTML\n- setValue(id, value) - Set input value\n- getValue(id) - Get input value\n- closest(id, selector) - Find closest ancestor\n- getElementById(id) - Get element by ID\n\n### State Atoms\n- get(key) - Get value from store\n- set(key, value) - Set value in store\n\n### Logic Atoms\n- if condition { } else { } - Conditional branch (condition can be variable or atom expression)\n- eq(a, b) - Equal comparison\n- not(value) - Logical NOT\n- isNil(value) - Check if null/undefined\n- and(a, b), or(a, b) - Logical AND/OR\n- gt(a, b), lt(a, b), gte(a, b), lte(a, b) - Numeric comparisons\n\n### Type Check Atoms\n- isNum(value) - Check if number\n- isStr(value) - Check if string\n- isArr(value) - Check if array\n- isObj(value) - Check if object\n\n### Math Atoms\n- add(a, b), sub(a, b), mul(a, b), div(a, b), mod(a, b) - Arithmetic\n- random(min, max) - Random number\n\n### String Atoms\n- concat(a, b) - Concatenate strings or arrays\n- format(template, ...keys) - Format string with {placeholder} syntax\n- split(text, separator) - Split string to array\n- contains(text, search) - Check if text contains substring\n- startsWith(text, prefix) - Check if text starts with prefix\n- replace(text, search, replacement) - Replace first occurrence\n- trim(text) - Remove whitespace from both ends\n- toLower(text) - Convert to lowercase\n- toUpper(text) - Convert to uppercase\n- slice(array|string, start, end?) - Slice array or substring\n\n### Type Conversion Atoms\n- toNum(value) - Convert to number (replaces parseFloat/parseInt)\n\n### Array Atoms\n- push(array, value) - Push to array\n- pop(array) - Pop from array\n- len(value) - Get length\n- getAt(array, index) - Get element at index\n- filter(array, nodes, itemKey) - Filter array with subgraph\n\n### Object Atoms\n- getProp(obj, key) - Get object property\n- setProp(obj, key, value) - Set object property\n- keys(obj) - Get object keys\n- values(obj) - Get object values\n- merge(a, b) - Merge two objects\n\n### Growth Creation (MOST IMPORTANT)\n- **save-growth(name, acs, type, icon, description)** - Create and register a growth. This is the ONLY way to save graphs. One call does: compile, validate, register to memory, persist to disk, update index, and write log. Returns { success: boolean, error?: string, path?: string }.\n  - name: Growth name, e.g. \"calculator\" or \"calculator/handle-digit\" for subgraphs\n  - acs: The ACS source code string\n  - type: \"app\" or \"tool\"\n  - icon: Emoji icon\n  - description: Short description\n  - Example: save-growth(name: \"calculator\", acs: \"graph calculator { ... }\", type: \"app\", icon: \"🧮\", description: \"Calculator\")\n\n### Control Flow Atoms\n- loop { } - Loop with optional max and cond\n- forEach item in array { } - Iterate array\n- exec(code) - Execute JavaScript\n- execFile(file) - Execute a graph file\n- execGraph(graph) - Execute a graph object\n\n### Time Atoms\n- now() - Current timestamp in milliseconds\n- timestampToDate(timestamp) - Convert timestamp to date object")
}
